00066 static StructRNA* rna_Sensor_refine(struct PointerRNA *ptr)
00067 {
00068     bSensor *sensor = (bSensor*)ptr->data;
00069 
00070     switch (sensor->type) {
00071         case SENS_ALWAYS:
00072             return &RNA_AlwaysSensor;
00073         case SENS_TOUCH:
00074             return &RNA_TouchSensor;
00075         case SENS_NEAR:
00076             return &RNA_NearSensor;
00077         case SENS_KEYBOARD:
00078             return &RNA_KeyboardSensor;
00079         case SENS_PROPERTY:
00080             return &RNA_PropertySensor;
00081         case SENS_ARMATURE:
00082             return &RNA_ArmatureSensor;
00083         case SENS_MOUSE:
00084             return &RNA_MouseSensor;
00085         case SENS_COLLISION:
00086             return &RNA_CollisionSensor;
00087         case SENS_RADAR:
00088             return &RNA_RadarSensor;
00089         case SENS_RANDOM:
00090             return &RNA_RandomSensor;
00091         case SENS_RAY:
00092             return &RNA_RaySensor;
00093         case SENS_MESSAGE:
00094             return &RNA_MessageSensor;
00095         case SENS_JOYSTICK:
00096             return &RNA_JoystickSensor;
00097         case SENS_ACTUATOR:
00098             return &RNA_ActuatorSensor;
00099         case SENS_DELAY:
00100             return &RNA_DelaySensor;
00101         default:
00102             return &RNA_Sensor;
00103     }
00104 }

00141 EnumPropertyItem *rna_Sensor_type_itemf(bContext *C, PointerRNA *ptr, PropertyRNA *UNUSED(prop), int *free)
00142 {
00143     EnumPropertyItem *item = NULL;
00144     Object *ob = NULL;
00145     int totitem = 0;
00146 
00147     if (ptr->type == &RNA_Sensor || RNA_struct_is_a(ptr->type, &RNA_Sensor)) {
00148         ob = (Object *)ptr->id.data;
00149     }
00150     else {
00151         /* can't use ob from ptr->id.data because that enum is also used by operators */
00152         ob = CTX_data_active_object(C);
00153     }
00154     
00155     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_ACTUATOR);
00156     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_ALWAYS);
00157 
00158     if (ob != NULL) {
00159         if (ob->type == OB_ARMATURE) {
00160             RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_ARMATURE);
00161         }
00162     }
00163     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_COLLISION);
00164     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_DELAY);
00165     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_JOYSTICK);
00166     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_KEYBOARD);
00167     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_MESSAGE);
00168     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_MOUSE);
00169     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_NEAR);
00170     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_PROPERTY);
00171     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_RADAR);
00172     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_RANDOM);
00173     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_RAY);
00174     RNA_enum_items_add_value(&item, &totitem, sensor_type_items, SENS_TOUCH);
00175     
00176     RNA_enum_item_end(&item, &totitem);
00177     *free = 1;
00178     
00179     return item;
00180 }

00233 static void rna_Sensor_Armature_update(Main *bmain, Scene *scene, PointerRNA *ptr)
00234 {
00235     bSensor *sens = (bSensor *)ptr->data;
00236     bArmatureSensor *as = sens->data;
00237     Object *ob = (Object *)ptr->id.data;
00238 
00239     char *posechannel = as->posechannel;
00240     char *constraint = as->constraint;
00241 
00242     /* check that bone exist in the active object */
00243     if (ob->type == OB_ARMATURE && ob->pose) {
00244         bPoseChannel *pchan;
00245         bPose *pose = ob->pose;
00246         for (pchan = pose->chanbase.first; pchan; pchan = pchan->next) {
00247             if (!strcmp(pchan->name, posechannel)) {
00248                 /* found it, now look for constraint channel */
00249                 bConstraint *con;
00250                 for (con = pchan->constraints.first; con; con = con->next) {
00251                     if (!strcmp(con->name, constraint)) {
00252                         /* found it, all ok */
00253                         return;
00254                     }
00255                 }
00256                 /* didn't find constraint, make empty */
00257                 constraint[0] = 0;
00258                 return;
00259             }
00260         }
00261     }
00262     /* didn't find any */
00263     posechannel[0] = 0;
00264     constraint[0] = 0;
00265 }
